autoresearch-mlx — Attribution and Lineage
==========================================

This repository is a maintained fork of:

    Trevin Peterson's autoresearch-mlx
    https://github.com/trevin-creator/autoresearch-mlx

Trevin authored the original Apple Silicon port, including the
initial versions of train.py, prepare.py, program.md, pyproject.toml,
and the public README. His commits remain in the git history of this
repository under his authorship.

Conceptual lineage
------------------

    Andrej Karpathy — the original autoresearch protocol; the
        "one mutable file / fixed time budget / keep-or-revert"
        loop design. https://github.com/karpathy/autoresearch

    Scott Casella — scasella/nanochat-mlx, an MLX reference for
        the GPT model and optimizer patterns.

    Awni Hannun — awni/picochat, MLX training patterns.

    Apple MLX team — the MLX array framework itself.
        https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx

